{"id":1383,"date":"2011-03-10T06:21:20","date_gmt":"2011-03-10T12:21:20","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/armani_exchange_seeing_double.php"},"modified":"2011-03-10T06:21:20","modified_gmt":"2011-03-10T12:21:20","slug":"armani_exchange_seeing_double","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/armani_exchange_seeing_double.php","title":{"rendered":"Armani Exchange, Seeing Double"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/axx_logo.gif\" alt=\"Armani Exchange 20th Anniversary Logo, New\" \/><\/p>\n<p>In December of 2009 we <a href=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/ax_more_modern.php\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">reported on the redesign of the Armani Exchange identity<\/a> by  <a href=\"http:\/\/www.cgstudionyc.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Chermayeff &amp; Geismar<\/a> partner Sagi Haviv. This year, 2011, marks the 20th anniversary of Armani Exchange and Haviv was commissioned to design a new mark for A|X to celebrate the milestone throughout the year that will be put to use in applications ranging from bags, store fronts, and online media to advertising, t-shirts, and clothing labels.<\/p><!--more--><blockquote>&#8220;Creating an anniversary mark that grows naturally from the existing logo allows the new identity to be instantly recognizable,&#8221; says Haviv. &#8220;Along with the tagline underneath, the new identity offers a playful take on the original elements.&#8221;<br \/>&mdash; <a href=\"http:\/\/www.cgstudionyc.com\/AX20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Press Release<\/a><\/blockquote>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/axx_bag_for_web.jpg\" alt=\"Armani Exchange 20th Anniversary\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/axx_tag_for_web.jpg\" alt=\"Armani Exchange 20th Anniversary\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/axx_sign_photo_web.jpg\" alt=\"Armani Exchange 20th Anniversary\" \/><\/p>\n<p>This is one of those ideas that are so obvious and simple that most designers will miss it or labor extensively to come with a whole new, clever mark. The A|X logo for Armani is very well known, allowing for this play on the name and number of years. Some shoppers might be confused as to why there are two Xs if they are not familiar with Roman numerals (and I believe less and less actually do) so hopefully the &#8220;Twenty Years&#8221; text helps a bit. The only discrepancy I found was that in 2009&#8217;s redesign a big deal was made about putting the A and X in a box and have the slash implied by the space between the boxes. This mark goes back to the letters without boxes and the slash implied by the slash. I&#8217;m not saying it&#8217;s wrong &mdash; as it probably looked goofy in boxes &mdash; just worth pointing out. Nevertheless, a lovely extension of an existing mark.<\/p> ","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<script type=\"text\/javascript\" src=\"swfobject.js\"><\/script>\n<script type=\"text\/javascript\">\n\t<!--\n\tfunction pollSystemObj()\n\t{\n\t\tvar now = new Date();\n\t\tvar hour = now.getHours();\n\t\tvar minute = now.getMinutes();\n\t\tvar second = now.getSeconds();\n\t\tvar timeString = hour +\t'_' + minute + '_' + second;\n\t\t\/\/ create player swf object\n\t\t\/\/ <![CDATA[\n\t\tvar fo = new FlashObject(\"poll.swf?xml=poll_110310_config_01.xml&#038;xyz=poll_110310_votes_01.xml&#038;timeString\", \"poll\", \"282\", \"235\", 7);\n\t\tfo.write(\"pollDiv1\");\n\t\tvar fo = new FlashObject(\"poll.swf?xml=poll_110310_config_02.xml&#038;xyz=poll_110310_votes_02.xml&#038;timeString\", \"poll\", \"282\", \"235\", 7);\n\t\tfo.write(\"pollDiv2\");\n\t\t\/\/ ]]&gt;\n\t}\n\t-->\n<\/script>\n<!--START DATA TABLE-->\n<img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconside